* L-values and R-values *

# L-value #                                 # R-value #
- has a name                                - does not have a name
- all variables are L-value                 - R-value is a temporary value
- can be assigned values                    - cannot be assigned values
- some expressions return L-value           - some expressions return R-value
- persist beyond the expression             - does not persist
- functions that return by reference,       - functions that return by value, return R-value
return L-value

* R-value References *
    - a reference created to a temporary
    - represents a temporary
    - created with && operator
    - cannot point to L-values